          <rect x="280" y="560" width="260" height="48" rx="8" fill="#10b981" stroke="#10b981" stroke-width="2"/>
          <text x="410" y="579" text-anchor="middle" font-size="16" fill="#ffffff">✅ 200 OK — Content Safe</text>
          <text x="410" y="598" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#ffffff">dare stored &amp; delivered</text>
        </g>
      </svg>
        </g>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <h3>Text-only Moderation</h3>
    <p>
      Used when a user types a dare without any image. The full pipeline (steps 1–5)
      runs on the dare text alone. If the dare passes, the client receives <code>200 OK</code>
      and can proceed to post.
    </p>

    <h3>Post moderation</h3>
    <p>
      Called after an image is already uploaded to Cloud Storage. Both the image <em>and</em>
      associated caption text are sent through the pipeline. The image is signed with a
      short-lived V4 URL so OpenAI can analyze it without the URL ever being public.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- 4. MEDIA PIPELINE -->
  <div class="section" id="media-pipeline">
    <h2>Media Upload Pipeline</h2>
    <p>Photos never go directly to our server. The client gets a short-lived signed URL and uploads straight to our Cloud Storage provider.</p>

    <div class="flow-wrap">
      <svg class="flow" viewBox="0 0 820 280" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <marker id="arr2" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto">
            <path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#333333"/>
          </marker>
          <marker id="arr2r" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto">
            <path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#ff3366"/>
          </marker>
          <marker id="arr2g" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto">
            <path d="M0,0 L0,6 L8,3 z" fill="#10b981"/>
          </marker>
        </defs>

        <!-- Client -->
        <rect x="20" y="30" width="140" height="44" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#eaeaea" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="90" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-size="16" fill="#1a1a1a">📱 Client</text>

        <line x1="160" y1="52" x2="220" y2="52" stroke="#333333" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arr2)"/>
        <text x="190" y="45" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#666666">① request</text>

        <!-- Server -->
        <rect x="222" y="14" width="190" height="76" rx="8" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#eaeaea" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="317" y="38" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#1a1a1a">Server</text>
        <text x="317" y="57" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#666666">• auth check</text>
        <text x="317" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#666666">• quota check</text>

        <line x1="412" y1="52" x2="490" y2="52" stroke="#333333" stroke-width="2" marker-end="url(#arr2)"/>
        <text x="451" y="44" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#666666">② signed</text>

        <!-- Cloud Storage -->
        <rect x="492" y="20" width="180" height="64" rx="8" fill="#eff6ff" stroke="#3b82f6" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="582" y="45" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#3b82f6">☁️ Cloud Storage</text>
        <text x="582" y="65" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#3b82f6">Signed URL</text>
        
        <!-- Client Moderation -->
        <path d="M 400,200 C 400,150 317,150 317,96" stroke="#10b981" stroke-width="2" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="5,4" marker-end="url(#arr2g)"/>

        <!-- Moderation trigger box -->
        <rect x="140" y="200" width="520" height="60" rx="8" fill="#ecfdf5" stroke="#10b981" stroke-width="2"/>
        <text x="400" y="225" text-anchor="middle" font-size="15" fill="#10b981">③ Client </text>
        <text x="400" y="247" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#10b981">→ Server signs image URL → client calls moderations pipeline</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="callout warn" data-label="Important">
      <p>
        If moderation fails at any point after the file has been uploaded,
        <code>file is cleaned up</code> from the Cloud Storage
        and the user's quota is restored.
        No dirty content stays in storage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 5. AUTH -->
  <div class="section" id="auth">
    <h2>Authentication &amp; Authorization</h2>
    <p>Every server endpoint is protected by <strong>JWT Auth verification</strong>. The token is decoded server-side.

    <div class="callout danger" data-label="Security alert">
      <p>
        Any request that fails this check is immediately rejected with <code>403 Forbidden</code>.
        The violation is logged as a <strong>SECURITY ALERT</strong> with the details to admin.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 6. STORAGE -->
